BUY NOW

What’s included in the bundle?

item.dc:creator: Eric Brünjes
item.description: Harmony is a playable vocal instrument, created by legendary hitmakers Curtis "Sauce" Wilson and Rochad Holiday, that captures the silky smooth articulation of R&B, the dusty texture of chopped hip-hop samples, and the glossy finesse of modern pop production. item.content:encoded:
Harmony is a playable vocal instrument, created by legendary hitmakers Curtis "Sauce" Wilson and Rochad Holiday, that captures the silky smooth articulation of R&B, the dusty texture of chopped hip-hop samples, and the glossy finesse of modern pop production.

Open FLEX and check the STORE tab to purchase, just $14.95 (USD) or included with FL Cloud Pro.

Learn more about Harmony

Harnessing stacked vocal samples and emotive phrases, Harmony turns vocal performances into lush pads, intimate leads, deep basses, and ethereal textures. Each take is captured and shaped to preserve its human nuance — delivering tone, musicality, and soul in every layer.

It also includes RIFF presets for creating original vocal runs with chopped licks mapped to key and scale — ideal for fluid melodies, spontaneous hooks, or quick embellishments. Paired with FLEX’s intuitive macro controls, you can sculpt tone, dynamics, and movement — unlocking vocal moments that bring your ideas to life and let your music truly sing.

Harmony contains 100 presets including:

  • 42 Vocal pad presets
  • 15 Key-split Riff presets (Riffs in left hand, pads in right)
  • 11 Arp
  • 7 Leads & keys
  • 7 Multi-channel presets (for Piano roll note color switching)
  • 18 Multi-layered source presets (including raw and FX versions)

Harmony — vocals reimagined.

Created by Curtis "Sauce" Wilson and Rochad Holiday whose credits include: Brandy, Ariana Grande, Ne-Yo, Celine Dion, Will Smith, Musiq Soulchild, Eric Benét, Eric Bellinger, Coco Jones, Muni Long, K. Michelle, Mary J. Blige, Mario, Amerie, Queen Naija, Keyshia Cole, and Fantasia.

N.B: A few sounds in the audio demo are not part of the pack and were added for context and inspiration.

FLEX is a preset-based synthesizer included free with FL Studio and driven by an advanced synthesis engine capable of Subtractive, Wavetable, Multisample, FM & AM based synthesis. The 8 Macros control custom synthesis targets, for each patch, and allow you to focus on what’s most important: making music. 

Available to purchase within FLEX in FL Studio or directly from Image-Line. The pack is also included in FL Cloud Pro. Find out more. 

Want to have your say about what FLEX packs we make in future?

Customers click through to our FLEX Pack Survey on the FL Studio Users forum (Looptalk) and vote now.

Enjoy!
item.metadata:description: Harmony is a vocal instrument blending smooth R&B, dusty hip-hop textures, and polished modern pop.

item.content:encoded:
Hypertrance by nuphory is a tribute to the golden era of trance — reimagined for today’s producers.

Inspired by analog gear, this pack fuses vintage grit with modern clarity to deliver raw, emotional, high-energy sounds.

Open FLEX and check the STORE tab to purchase, just $14.95 (USD) or included with FL Cloud Pro.

Learn more about Hypertrance by nuphory


From lush pads and soaring supersaws to distorted bass and hypnotic arps, every preset captures the spirit of trance pioneers like Darude, Tiësto, and Ferry Corsten — as well as modern innovators like Ilan Bluestone and Maddix.

Whether you’re building a nostalgic throwback or a fresh take on trance, Hypertrance by nuphory gives you the tools to create music that moves. Perfect for trance, melodic techno, psy-influenced builds, and more.

Contains 100 Presets, including:

  • 11 acid
  • 37 basses
  • 12 chords
  • 25 leads
  • 15 pads

Bring the rave back. Feel the rush again. Create something euphoric.

The 8 Macros control custom synthesis targets, for each patch, and allow you to focus on what’s most important: making music. 

Available to purchase within FLEX in FL Studio or directly from Image-Line. The pack is also included in FL Cloud Pro. Find out more. 

nuphory is a music producer and FL Studio Power User. Find out more.

The long awaited follow up to Chill-Lo-Fi 1, immerse your beats into deep-sampled pianos, vintage digital keys, and cosy synth tones. Open FLEX and check the STORE tab to purchase, just $14.95 (USD) or included with FL Cloud Pro.

Learn more about Chill-Lo-Fi-2

Inside you’ll find felt-muted chords, picked and plucked textures, and warm, warbly leads pulled from classic FM and sample-based synths, early digital workstations, and crunchy vintage keyboards.

Whether they’re warmed with VHS or sent into orbit with custom reverbs, the sounds are lo-fi at its most lush — perfect for anything from fluttering melodies to gentle noise layers.

What's included

Chill-Lo-Fi 2 contains 195 presets, including:

  • 98 keys

Inject new energy into your lo-fi productions.

item.dc:creator: Eric Brünjes
item.description: Step into the world of metallic chaos and organic weirdness with Glitch Form, the ultimate sound design toolkit for experimental music makers. Perfect for genres like glitch, breakcore, braindance, IDM, bass, or anything you’re ready to throw into the mix, this pack is built for the fringes. Open FLEX and...
item.content:encoded:
Step into the world of metallic chaos and organic weirdness with Glitch Form, the ultimate sound design toolkit for experimental music makers. Perfect for genres like glitch, breakcore, braindance, IDM, bass, or anything you’re ready to throw into the mix, this pack is built for the fringes. Open FLEX and check the STORE tab to purchase, just $14.95 (USD) or included with FL Cloud Pro.

Learn more about Glitch Form

Prepare for pure sonic mayhem with wobbling basses, morphing pads, and synth lines that twist and turn like a caffeinated thought — only to be snatched back in an instant. Sourced from classic analog synths, prepared pianos, and modular rigs (held together with duct tape and dreams), this collection is all about trippy, unpredictable, beautifully broken sound design.

With 114 presets to choose from, including:

  • 19 Acid sounds
  • 3 Arp sounds
  • 6 Basses
  • 1 Chord
  • 8 Drum patches
  • 12 Keyboards
  • 15 Leads
  • 25 Pads
  • 8 Sequences
  • 4 SFX

Whether you're crafting your next glitch masterpiece or pushing your genre boundaries, Glitch Form is your gateway to mind-bending sonic experimentation. Get ready to break everything you thought you knew about sound.

Glitch Form is available to purchase within FLEX in FL Studio or directly from Image-Line.

The pack is also included in FL Cloud Pro. Find out more.

Don't miss out on this essential addition to your sound library.
item.metadata:description: Step into metallic chaos and organic weirdness with Glitch Form, the latest FLEX Pack for experimental music makers.

item.content:encoded:
We are excited to introduce the Friends of FL Studio Plugin Bundle — an exclusive collection of 19 premium plugins from renowned developers MeldaProduction, W. A. Production, and UnitedPlugins, now available at an incredible 90% discount!

Running from March 20 to April 3, 2025, this limited-time offer is designed to give you access to high-quality tools for a fraction of the regular price.

GET THE BUNDLE

What’s Inside?

This bundle is packed with powerful plugins that cover everything from sound design and mixing to creative effects and workflow enhancements. A standout is Babylon 2, a versatile wavetable synth — giving FL Studio users access to a powerful synthesis tool not found in the native lineup. Here’s what you get:

MeldaProduction:

  • MUnison
  • MChorusMB
  • MSoundFactoryLE
  • MTurboReverbLE

W. A. Production:

  • Babylon 2 + Wavetable Expansions
  • InstaComposer 2 + all current and future Expansions
  • Trivox
  • BeatQuake
  • KickShaper
  • ChromaBox

UnitedPlugins:

  • Voxessor
  • TrapTune
  • FireSpacer
  • FireMaximizer
  • QuickMuse
  • BassRift
  • Cyberdrive
  • Dropkick
  • MorphVerb

The combined MSRP of the included plugins is €1,848/$1,848, but for just €149/$149, you can get your hands on the entire collection.

Whether you’re a beginner or a seasoned pro, this collection of plugins will help you take your music to the next level. From lush reverbs and deep bass enhancers to dynamic vocal processors and creative effects, you’ll have everything you need to refine your sound and boost your creativity.

Time-limited offer

Available from March 20 to April 3, 2025, exclusively through Image-Line. 

For more details visit the dedicated page here.

item.content:encoded:
FLEX Mainroom Techno is the latest FLEX pack designed to bring raw energy to all subgenres of techno. Packed with the heaviest kicks and low-end rumbles, pulsating acid lines, and deep, atmospheric synths, this collection is crafted to ignite the dancefloor. Open FLEX and check the STORE tab to purchase, just $14.95 (USD) or included with FL Cloud Pro.

Learn more about Mainroom Techno

Developed by sound designer Saif Sameer, Mainroom Techno combines digital and analog sources to deliver razor-sharp synthesis, dark textures, and floor-shaking dynamics — all with undeniable authenticity. From twisted FX to hypnotic arpeggios, every preset has been meticulously designed to cut through the mix and provide unparalleled depth.

What's included

The pack includes 150 presets, featuring:

  • 8 Acid sounds
  • 16 Arpeggios
  • 10 Atmospheres
  • 15 Basses
  • 13 Bass sequences
  • 21 Chord stabs
  • 7 Drums & percussions
  • 23 Leads
  • 4 Pads
  • 9 Plucks
  • 10 Sequences
  • 3 Sound effects
  • 8 Synths
  • 3 Vocal snippets

Inspired by the best

Drawing inspiration from top techno artists like Adam Beyer, Charlotte de Witte, Amelie Lens, Victor Ruiz, and Reinier Zonneveld, this pack is built for producers looking for modern-sounding club-ready tracks.

Mainroom Techno is available to purchase within FLEX in FL Studio or directly from Image-Line.

The pack is also included in FL Cloud Pro. Find out more.

Don't miss out on this essential addition to your sound library.
